s fascinating book, Manning recreates the story of how these private, secretive practices became a matter of national interest, concern, and fantasy. Looking at personal expressions of love and the circulation of these narratives at the broader public level of the modern nation, Love Stories offers an ethnography of language and desire that doubles as an introduction to key linguistic genres and to the interplay of language and culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aEthnology - Georgia (Republic) - Xevsureti. 0aEthnologyzGeorgia (Republic)zXevsuretʻi. 0aEthnologyzGeorgia (Republic). 0aKhevsursxSexual behavior. 0aKhevsursxSocial life and customs. 0aKhevsurs--Sexual behavior. 4aCoursebook. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144260898640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442608986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442608986/original  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK